# Master Specification: Project Digital Plaid (Final)

## I. Technical Architecture & Stack
- **Frontend**: React Native (Expo) with NativeWind.
- **Backend**: Supabase (Auth, PostgreSQL, Edge Functions).
- **Offline-First Resilience**: Mandatory local caching (SQLite/AsyncStorage). The app must allow "Check-ins" and "Recalibrations" without internet, syncing to the cloud when signal returns.
- **Battery Strategy**:
    - **No Background GPS**: Location is inferred from the "Last Completed Step."
    - **Lazy Fetching**: Data pings only on Step Completion, Manual Recalibration, or Mobile Order triggers.
- **Platform**: Initially a PWA (to bypass friction), moving to Native for Live Activity (Lock Screen) support.

## II. Core Feature Set
### 1. The Multi-Guest Intake System
- **Demographics**: Name, Age, Gender, and Height (Mandatory for Rider Switch).
- **Link-Share Surveys**: Party Leader sends a unique link to each guest.
- **Can-Act-On-Behalf**: Leader can fill out or skip surveys for those who can't (toddlers/seniors).
- **Preference Matrix**:
    - **Rides**: Must-Do, Like-to-Do, Will Avoid.
    - **Characters**: Must-Meet, Like-to-Meet, Avoid.
    - **Foodie Profile**: Allergies (automated menu filtering), Cuisine (Adventurous/Safe), Dining Style, and **Snack Habit**.
- **Ambition Metric**: "The Completionist" vs. "The Relaxed Parent."
- **Stamina Check**: "Walking Capacity" score (1–10) to cluster activities and minimize cross-park trekking.

### 2. 2026 Temporal Rule Engine
- **Dynamic Switching**: Logic sets flip per day based on ParkID (WDW vs. DL).
- **Resort Rules**:
    - **WDW (4 Parks)**: Pre-booking (7/3 days), LL Multi Pass Tiers (1 Tier-1, 2 Tier-2), and 45-min transport buffers.
    - **DL Resort (DL/DCA)**: Day-of booking, **5-min walking buffers between gates**, and DCA 25th Anniversary event overlays.
- **2026 Exclusions**: Hard-coded for Big Thunder (WDW), Buzz Lightyear (WDW), Rock 'n' Roller Coaster (Muppet retheme March 2), Jungle Cruise (DL), and Space Mountain (DL).
- **Special Events**: Support for Hard-Ticket parties (Not-So-Scary) and EPCOT Festivals (Booth Crawl logic).

### 3. Tactical Coach & "Family Peace" Logic
- **Rider Switch Double-Block**: 1.5x duration multiplier for height conflicts. Generates a "Waiting Parent Sub-Step."
- **Character Interaction Engine**: Alerts 15m before a "Must-Meet" character appears.
- **Task Killer**: Character Dining automatically marks those characters as "Met."
- **Mobile Order Watchdog**:
    - **Hanger Prevention**: Suggests "Snack Clusters" based on location and **Snack Habit** preference.
    - **Lead-Time Alerts**: [Target Meal Time] - [Current Kitchen Return Time] - 10m Buffer.
- **Recalibration (Tolerance)**: Only prompts a pivot if a Must-Do wait increases by >20 mins or a ride closes.
- **Persona**: "Tactical Expert" coach—Expert context, **non-condescending**, narrative style.

### 4. Mini Memory Maker (Recap)
- **Planned vs. Actual**: Vertical side-by-side timeline of the day.
- **Trophy Room**: "Wait Time Defeated" (Minutes saved) and "Characters High-Fived."
- **Joy Graph**: Mapping user-submitted emojis/sentiment against the daily timeline.
- **Memory Note**: Prompt for a high-point description + photo upload.
- **Nudge Log**: Captures completed "Contextual Nudges" (Photo-ops, Hidden Mickeys, Sensory Cues).

## III. UX/UI Design Philosophy
- **Theme**: "Executive Plaid" (Forest Green #1B3022, Cream #F4F1DE, Gold #D4AF37).
- **Sunlight Mode**: Ultra-high contrast, 16pt+ sans-serif fonts.
- **One-Handed Navigation**: All interactive elements focused in the bottom 30% of the screen.
- **Touch Targets**: Minimum 48x48 pixels.
- **Nudge Triggers**: Text-based, itinerary-linked (e.g., "Look for the key under the mat at Muppet*Vision").
- **Recalibrate Button**: Requires a **2-second hold** to prevent accidental triggers.
